definitions.definition: In the end ; at some later time, especially after a long time, a series of problems, struggles, delays or setbacks.
examples: Everyone's true colors will be revealed eventually .
She didn't arrive. Eventually , we started without her.
He hopes eventually to attend nursing school.

definitions.definition: For some tail ; for all terms beyond some term; with only finitely many exceptions.
examples: Eventually , all prime numbers are odd.
I will come eventually , but haven't decided yet.

main_definition: In the end ; at some later time, especially after a long time, a series of problems, struggles, delays or setbacks.
secondary_definitions: ( mathematics , of a sequence ) For some tail ; for all terms beyond some term; with only finitely many exceptions.
( proscribed , non-native speakers ' English ) Possibly , potentially , perhaps .
